title: More than 150 injured in clash at Eritrean Embassy event in Tel Aviv
description: The melee was the latest violence to break out at an Eritrean-sponsored festival abroad intended to celebrate 30 years of Eritrean independence.

title: Nobel Prize foundation scraps plan to invite Russia, Belarus after criticism
description: The Nobel Foundation said it would no longer invite Belarus and Russia’s ambassadors to the Stockholm awards ceremony, after objections from Ukraine and Sweden.

title: McCain’s political heirs carry on his fight against Trumpian isolationism
description: The institute bearing John McCain’s name says the Republican Party’s retreat from its strong national security stance would shock the senator if he were alive.

title: How wildfires are threatening the Mediterranean way of life
description: Wildfires in Greece and beyond have been turning virgin forest into preternatural moonscapes and devastating monasteries, tavernas, vineyards and olive groves.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russia says new ICBM is on ‘combat duty’; U.S. highlights Kyiv’s advances
description: Moscow’s announcement on the nuclear-capable Sarmat missile came shortly after Kyiv claimed it hit a target with new domestically made long-range missiles.
